HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1130
By Capley
A RESOLUTION to honor and recognize Samantha McNabb,
2026 Valedictorian of Wayne County High
School.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that the members of this General Assembly should pause to pay
tribute to those students who, through their natural talents and unflagging commitment to
academic excellence, have distinguished themselves in the classroom; and
WHEREAS, Samantha McNabb is one such exceptional student, who was recently
named the Valedictorian of the 2026 graduating class at Wayne County High School; and
WHEREAS, through diligent study, steady composure during examinations, and
steadfast commitment of time and talent, Ms. McNabb has achieved outstanding academic
success and joined the ranks of the best and brightest students in Tennessee and our country;
and
WHEREAS, in her remarkable high school career, Samantha McNabb has earned an
exemplary 100 grade point average while participating in numerous extracurricular activities,
including the Math Club, Beta Club, Book Club, and Interact Club, as well as serving as vice
president of the Wayne County chapter of FFA, being voted Most Intelligent by her peers, and
accumulating over 130 hours of community service; and
WHEREAS, her display of intellectual aptitude and ambition surely bodes well for her
future success as a student at the University of North Alabama, where she will study data
analytics; and
WHEREAS, Samantha McNabb's noteworthy achievement is a tremendous source of
pride for her parents, Darian and Tanya McNabb, her school, and her community; and
WHEREAS, Ms. McNabb's dedication to excellence is clearly deserving of the respect,
admiration, and commendation of this General Assembly; now, therefore,
HJR1130
014719
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we hereby commend and honor the 2026 Wayne County High School
Valedictorian, Samantha McNabb, on her impressive academic achievement and extend to her
our best wishes for a happy, successful future.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
